In [28]:
import pandas as pd
from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize
from nltk.stem import SnowballStemmer
data = {'text': ['This is a sample text.', 'Another example here.', 'Yet another sentence.']}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)
def textprocessing(text, stuff_to_be_removed=None):
    if stuff_to_be_removed is None:
        stuff_to_be_removed = []  
    text_tokens = word_tokenize(text) 
    lem = SnowballStemmer("english")
    text = [lem.stem(word) for word in text_tokens if not word in stuff_to_be_removed] 
    text1 = " ".join(text)
    return text1
df['processed_text'] = df['text'].apply(lambda x: textprocessing(x, stuff_to_be_removed=['is', 'a', 'here']))
print(df[['text', 'processed_text']])

                     text       processed_text
0  This is a sample text.    this sampl text .
1   Another example here.       anoth exampl .
2   Yet another sentence.  yet anoth sentenc .

from wordcloud import WordCloud
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
negative_tweets = df[df['sentiment'] == 'negative']
negative_text = ' '.join(negative_tweets['text'])
if len(negative_text) > 0:
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='black').generate(negative_text)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()
else:
    print("No negative text to generate a word cloud.")
